title: Latest Sun Sentinel Cross Country Results (Sept. 10)
text:
Thursday's only cross country event was the boca Raton Invitational.
Broward write-up
Katie Pinnell led a trio of North Broward Prep runners to place top-10 and propel the Eagles to a team win at the Boca Raton Invitational Thursday.
Pinnell was the girls’ overal winner with a time of 20:33. Teammates Katie Bishop (20:55) and Gianna Milan (22:04) finished fourth and eighth respectively.
On the Boys’ side, John I. Leonard’s Ilio Sanchez won with a time of 16:45. He also led the Lancers to a team win.
Coral Springs’ Khiro Hoilett was Broward’s best finisher, in sixth place with a time of 17:52.
Coral Glades also saw a pair of top-10 finishers in Andres Torrente (ninth place, 18:16) and Dominick Deleva (10th place, 18:17).
Caitlyn Wurzburger also finished in the top-10, coming in at ninth place for American Heritage with 22:14.
Palm Beach write-up
Ilio Sanchez was the fastest runner Thursday, helping John I. Leonard to a team win at the Boca Raton Invitational.
Sanchez, with a time of 16:45, wasn’t the only Lancer to finish in the top-10. Teammates Kurt Taegar (17:37) finished in fourth place, while Jose Rivera (18:11) came in eighth place.
On the girls’ side, North Broward Prep’s Katie Pinnell won with a time of 20:33, also leading the Eagles to a first-place team finish.
Boca Raton finished in second place for both the boys and the girls. Nicholas Evans was the only top-10 finisher for the Bobcats. He placed second with a time of 17:00. Victoria Stewart made a top-five appearance with a time of 20:59.
Other notable Palm Beach performances include Jupiter Christian’s Josh Skielnik (third place, 17:25), Wellington’s Samuel Weingart (fifth place, 17:50) and from St. Andrew’s, Maya Belezany (second place, 20:39) and Cassandra Lawlor (third place, 20:45).
